@@ -0,0 +1,181 @@
+# Change-by-change breakdown
+
+Covers every change outside of `v4/`, `templates/go`, and generated files.
+
+---
+
+## New file: `internal/gir/types/imports.go`
+
+**Why:** Previously, imports were not computed during generation. The template had a hardcoded import block and `goimports` was run afterwards to fix them. This file replaces that approach by tracking imports as types are resolved.
+
+- **`ImportConfig` struct** — Holds module paths and a `PackageImports` map (namespace name -> Go import path). This replaces the old hardcoded `V4Packages` allowlist and `ModuleBase` constant, making the generator work with any module layout.
+- **`ImportConfig.AddPackages()`** — Helper to bulk-register namespaces from an external dependency under a given module+prefix. Used by the example to register puregotk's namespaces.
+- **`ImportSet` struct** — Per-file import accumulator. Created via `NewImportSet(pkgName, config)` and threaded through all type-resolution functions.
+- **`AddPkg(pkg)`** — Looks up the package in `PackageImports` and adds the import. Replaces the old pattern of hardcoding `ModuleBase + "/v4/" + pkg`.
+- **`AddCore()`** — Uses `CoreModule` (falling back to `ModuleBase`) so `pkg/core` always resolves to puregotk's module even when generating a third-party library.
+- **`AddPurego()`, `AddUnsafe()`, `AddStructs()`** — Straightforward single-import helpers.
+- **`AddTypes()`** — Looks up `gobject` in `PackageImports` and appends `/types`. Needed for files that reference `types.GType`.
+- **`TrackGoType(goType)`** — Scans a Go type string for `pkg.` prefixes and calls `AddPkg` for each match. This is the main mechanism for automatically adding imports from type references like `glib.Error` or `gtk.Widget`.
+- **`Sorted()`** — Returns imports grouped: stdlib first, blank line separator, then third-party. This replaces the old plain alphabetical sort that mixed stdlib and third-party imports.
+
+---
+
+## `internal/gir/types/template.go`
+
+### `AddAPI`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter
+
+**Why:** This function generates API-level call expressions like `glib.NewCallback(x)` or `gobject.ConvertPtr(x)`. Previously those cross-package references were left for `goimports` to resolve. Now the import is recorded at the exact point where the reference is created.
+
+- **Callback case** — When `glibNs != ""`, calls `imps.AddPkg("glib")` because the generated code references `glib.NewCallback`.
+- **Classes/Interfaces `stars > 1` case** — When `gobjectNs != ""`, calls `imps.AddPkg("gobject")` because the generated code references `gobject.ConvertPtr`.
+- **End of function** — Calls `imps.TrackGoType(t)` on the final API type to catch any remaining cross-package type references.
+
+### `AddPure`: comment placement fix
+
+**Why:** The comments "Out parameters are always pointers in C" and "For primitive Go types we need to manually add the *" were inside the `if stars == 0` block but describe the outer `if isOut` block. Moved them to the correct scope. No code change.
+
+### `Add`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter
+
+**Why:** Passes the import set through to `AddAPI` so imports are tracked for every parameter.
+
+### `AddThrows`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter
+
+**Why:** When a function has `throws="1"`, the generated code references `**glib.Error`. The import for `glib` must be recorded. Previously left for `goimports`.
+
+### `Fmt`: removed trailing `\n` from `cerr` write
+
+**Why:** The template uses `{{- with .Ret.Fmt ...}}` to conditionally emit the return formatting. If `Fmt` returns a string ending in `\n`, the template produces a blank line before the closing `}` of the function. Removing the `\n` lets the template control the whitespace.
+
+---
+
+## `internal/gir/types/interface.go`
+
+### `ConvertInterface`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter
+
+**Why:** Interface methods and properties need import tracking just like class methods.
+
+- **TypeGetter** — If the interface has a `GLibGetType`, records the `types` import.
+- **Method parameters/returns** — Passes `imps` through to `Parameters.Template` and `ReturnValue.Template`.
+- **Cross-namespace interfaces** — When an interface from another namespace (e.g., `Gio.ActionMap` used by `Gtk.Application`) has methods that survive the `implemented` filter, records the interface's namespace import via `imps.AddPkg(ins)`.
+- **Properties** — Passes `imps` through to `prop.Template`.
+
+### `GetInterfaceFuncs`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter
+
+**Why:** Passes through to `ConvertInterface`.
+
+---
+
+## `internal/gir/types/types.go`
+
+### `Parameters.Template`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter + throws fix
+
+**Why (imps):** Passes the import set through to `Add` and `AddThrows`.
+
+**Why (throws fix):** The function had two early returns (when `p == nil` and when `len(params) == 0`) that returned an empty `funcArgsTemplate{}` without checking `throws`. This meant `throws="1"` functions with no regular parameters (e.g., `g_async_result_legacy_propagate_error`) never got the `&cerr` argument added. The fix checks `throws` before each early return and calls `AddThrows` if needed.
+
+### `Property.Template`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter + import tracking
+
+**Why:** Properties generate code that references `gobject.Value`, `glib.StrvGetType()`, `core.UnsafeSlice()`, and `unsafe.Pointer`. Previously these were left for `goimports`. Now the exact imports needed are recorded based on the property's GValue type, whether it's readable/writable, and whether it's a boxed type.
+
+### `ReturnValue.Template`: added `imps *ImportSet` parameter + import tracking
+
+**Why:** Return values that are classes from other namespaces (e.g., `*gtk.Widget`) need their namespace imported. Also, classes with `transfer-ownership="none"` generate `gobject.IncreaseRef(cret)`, which needs the `gobject` import. Both are now tracked at the point where the return type is resolved.
+
+---
+
+## `internal/gir/pass/pass.go`
+
+### New imports: `bytes`, `context`, `go/format`, `log`, `sync`, `errgroup`
+
+**Why:** `Second()` now formats files in-process with `go/format.Source` instead of shelling out to `goimports`/`gofumpt`, and parallelizes both template execution and formatting with `errgroup`.
+
+### `Pass` struct: added `ImpConfig *types.ImportConfig`
+
+**Why:** Holds the import configuration passed in by the caller.
+
+### `New()`: added `config *types.ImportConfig` parameter
+
+**Why:** The caller provides the module base, path prefix, purego module, and optionally pre-populated package imports.
+
+### `First()`: builds `PackageImports` from parsed repositories
+
+**Why:** After collecting type information, iterates all parsed namespaces and registers their import paths (using `ModuleBase`/`PathPrefix`). Pre-populated entries (from external dependencies) are preserved.
+
+### New type: `perFile` struct
+
+**Why:** Replaces the old pattern of separate `map[string][]T` for each type category (aliases, enums, records, etc.) plus no import tracking. Each `perFile` bundles all generated elements for a single output file together with its `ImportSet`, making it clear what belongs to what.
+
+### `writeGo()`: added `rawFiles *[]string` parameter, refactored to use `perFile`
+
+**Why (rawFiles):** Collects output file paths so `Second()` can format them afterwards.
+
+**Why (perFile):** The old code used separate maps (`aliases[fn]`, `records[fn]`, etc.) and a `files []string` slice to track which files existed. The new code uses a single `files map[string]*perFile` with a `getFile()` helper that lazily creates entries. Each processing loop gets the file's `ImportSet` and records imports as types are resolved.
+
+### Specific import tracking additions in `writeGo()`:
+
+- **Bitfields/Enums with TypeGetter** — `imps.AddTypes()` because the generated code references `types.GType`.
+- **Constants** — `imps.TrackGoType(ct.Type)` because constant types may reference other packages.
+- **Records with TypeGetter** — `imps.AddTypes()`.
+- **Record callback fields** — `imps.AddPurego()` + `imps.AddUnsafe()` because callback accessor wrappers use `purego.NewCallback` and `unsafe.Pointer`.
+- **Record non-callback fields** — `imps.TrackGoType(_type)` because field types may reference other packages.
+- **Callbacks** — Uses a throwaway `ImportSet` because the callback type definition only renders `Pure.Types` and `Ret.Raw`; the API-level return type (which may reference a cross-package class) must not leak into the file's imports. Only the actually-rendered types are tracked via the file's real `ImportSet`.
+- **Classes with TypeGetter** — `imps.AddTypes()`.
+- **Signals** — `imps.AddPurego()`, `imps.AddUnsafe()`, `imps.AddPkg("glib")`, `imps.AddPkg("gobject")` because signal connection code uses all four.
+- **Class parent** — `imps.TrackGoType(parent)` because the parent struct may be from another package.
+- **needsInit** — `pf.imps.AddPurego()` + `pf.imps.AddCore()` because the `init()` function uses `purego.Dlopen` and `core.PuregoSafeRegister`.
+- **Records present** — `pf.imps.AddStructs()` + `pf.imps.AddUnsafe()` because record structs use `structs.HostLayout` and `unsafe.Pointer` in `GoPointer()`.
+
+### `writeGo()`: template output to buffer + file
+
+**Why:** Old code used `os.Create` + `gotemp.Execute(f, args)` writing directly to a file. New code writes to a `bytes.Buffer` first, then `os.WriteFile`. This is needed because `go/format.Source` needs the complete source as a byte slice.
+
+### `writeGo()`: `TemplateArg` now includes `Imports` field
+
+**Why:** The template's import block is now populated from `pf.imps.Sorted()` instead of being hardcoded.
+
+### `Second()`: parallel execution + in-process formatting
+
+**Why:** Old code was `for _, r := range p.Parsed { p.writeGo(r, gotemp, dir) }` — sequential, no formatting. New code:
+1. Runs `writeGo` for each repository concurrently via `errgroup`, collecting output file paths under a mutex.
+2. Runs `go/format.Source` on each output file concurrently via a second `errgroup`.
+
+This replaces the old `gen.sh` pipeline of `goimports` + `gofumpt` + `goimports` + `go vet`.
+
+---
+
+## `pkg/gir/pass/pass.go`
+
+### Added `ImportConfig` type alias
+
+**Why:** Re-exports `types.ImportConfig` so that callers using the public API (`pkg/gir/pass`) can construct an `ImportConfig` without importing the internal `types` package directly.
+
+---
+
+## `gen.go`
+
+### `pass.New()` now receives `ImportConfig`
+
+**Why:** Configures the generator with `ModuleBase: "codeberg.org/puregotk/puregotk"`, `PathPrefix: "v4"`, `PuregoModule: "codeberg.org/puregotk/purego"`. Namespaces are auto-discovered from the GIR files.
+
+### Added `"nl"` template function
+
+**Why:** The template needs to emit newlines that survive Go template whitespace trimming (`{{-` / `-}}`). `{{nl}}` calls a Go function returning `"\n"`, which is output text (not template whitespace) and therefore immune to trimming. Used in the `init()` block of `templates/go` to separate registration groups.
+
+---
+
+## `examples/mylib-gtk-meson-go/gen.go`
+
+### Extract puregotk namespace names from GIR filenames
+
+**Why:** The example generates a custom library that imports puregotk's v4 packages. Those packages live under a different module path than the example itself. The namespace names are extracted from filenames (e.g., `Gtk-4.0.gir` -> `Gtk`) so they can be pre-registered.
+
+### `ImportConfig` with `ModuleBase`, `CoreModule`, and `AddPackages`
+
+**Why:**
+- `ModuleBase` is set to the example's own module so its local namespace (`mylibgtkmeson`) gets the correct import path.
+- `CoreModule` is set to puregotk's module so `pkg/core` resolves correctly.
+- `config.AddPackages("codeberg.org/puregotk/puregotk", "v4", puregotkNamespaces)` pre-registers all puregotk namespaces with their correct import paths before `First()` runs.
+
+### Added `"nl"` template function
+
+**Why:** Same as `gen.go` — the template requires this function.
